WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.879 --> 00:00:03.939
You know what time it is?
I have to sleep.

2
00:00:05.083 --> 00:00:06.983
Hey. fatso. eat shit and die!

3
00:00:07.886 --> 00:00:09.376
Die? In this racket?

4
00:00:09.555 --> 00:00:11.580
Sorry. sorry!

5
00:00:13.892 --> 00:00:15.883
Get out of my way!

6
00:00:16.662 --> 00:00:18.391
Hang in there. Tailor.

7
00:00:27.372 --> 00:00:29.499
Be quiet!

8
00:00:34.746 --> 00:00:39.479
Give us a break! Why push us so far?

9
00:00:54.166 --> 00:00:55.360
There's another master?

10
00:03:22.481 --> 00:03:24.472
It's the Lion's Roar!

11
00:03:25.150 --> 00:03:26.981
I thought that was a myth.

12
00:03:28.186 --> 00:03:31.155
Who knew the Lion's Roar
really exists?

13
00:03:31.323 --> 00:03:34.918
That's the last we'll see of them.

14
00:03:38.096 --> 00:03:40.428
It's bad. Brother Sum.
Quick. start the car!

15
00:03:40.799 --> 00:03:42.426
Start the car!

16
00:03:49.174 --> 00:03:50.334
Boss!

17
00:03:50.509 --> 00:03:52.773
Keep it down! Have you no manners?

18
00:03:52.944 --> 00:03:55.344
Get lost. People are trying to sleep.

19
00:03:55.514 --> 00:03:58.483
They have to work tomorrow.
Get out of here!

20
00:04:01.720 --> 00:04:03.347
Scumbags!

21
00:05:29.207 --> 00:05:32.233
I can't hang on much longer.

22
00:05:34.613 --> 00:05:38.481
But having seen
real masters like you...

23
00:05:39.217 --> 00:05:41.276
...I can now die in peace.

24
00:05:41.453 --> 00:05:43.387
Don't say that.

25
00:05:43.555 --> 00:05:46.490
We're ordinary folks.

26
00:05:46.658 --> 00:05:48.421
Ordinary's a blessing.

27
00:05:48.593 --> 00:05:52.051
Don't call us masters.

28
00:05:52.230 --> 00:05:54.130
But you're such great fighters!

29
00:05:54.299 --> 00:05:58.565
If only you'd helped earlier.
they wouldn't have to die this way.

30
00:05:59.070 --> 00:06:03.234
Like Donut said.
everyone has his reasons.

31
00:06:04.009 --> 00:06:05.738
Years ago...

32
00:06:06.244 --> 00:06:09.338
...we saw our only son killed in a fight.

33
00:06:11.616 --> 00:06:14.278
Revenge can be devastating.

34
00:06:14.653 --> 00:06:16.814
Do you understand?

35
00:06:16.988 --> 00:06:20.082
Why don't you train us
to be top fighters...

36
00:06:20.258 --> 00:06:23.250
...and we'll avenge them!

37
00:06:23.595 --> 00:06:27.588
Becoming a top fighter takes time.

38
00:06:27.766 --> 00:06:30.326
Unless you're a natural-born
kung-fu genius.

39
00:06:30.502 --> 00:06:34.268
And they're one in a million.

40
00:06:41.846 --> 00:06:44.041
It's obvious I'm the one!

41
00:06:47.619 --> 00:06:49.814
Don't think so.

42
00:06:50.789 --> 00:06:56.159
Everyone! We swore
we'd never fight again.

43
00:06:56.328 --> 00:06:58.728
But we broke that promise today.

44
00:06:58.897 --> 00:07:02.458
For your own safety. please all leave!

45
00:07:06.905 --> 00:07:10.466
In great power lies great responsibility.

46
00:07:10.976 --> 00:07:12.841
There's no escaping from it.

47
00:07:13.245 --> 00:07:15.805
Donut. you're hurt bad.

48
00:07:15.981 --> 00:07:17.539
Rest now.

49
00:07:22.487 --> 00:07:24.921
We can't understand
what you're saying.

50
00:07:26.558 --> 00:07:27.650
Donut!

51
00:07:40.705 --> 00:07:42.696
I know you. four-eyes!

52
00:07:44.109 --> 00:07:48.705
You seem prejudiced against
the sight-challenged.

53
00:07:48.880 --> 00:07:52.179
That's right.
Especially gold-framed four-eyes.

54
00:07:56.421 --> 00:07:59.754
Gold frames are perfect for clerks.

55
00:07:59.924 --> 00:08:03.018
I think I look good.
So why keep picking on me?

56
00:08:05.397 --> 00:08:06.386
Help me!

57
00:08:08.733 --> 00:08:11.964
"Help me! Help me!"
Want to play. punks?

58
00:08:12.137 --> 00:08:13.968
The Dragon Style? The Tiger Style?

59
00:08:18.710 --> 00:08:23.147
Come down here. and I'll smash
your glasses. Come on!

60
00:08:24.816 --> 00:08:27.046
You know I'd do it. right?

61
00:08:28.386 --> 00:08:29.717
Swear to it!

62
00:08:30.322 --> 00:08:31.653
Swear!

63
00:08:34.492 --> 00:08:38.792
Have you no respect? Where were you
when I needed you?

64
00:08:40.565 --> 00:08:42.260
You sound like a wimp!

65
00:08:42.434 --> 00:08:45.597
We always get beat!
We haven't gotten anywhere.

66
00:08:45.770 --> 00:08:49.501
No killing. no arson.
no robberies. no rapes...

67
00:08:49.674 --> 00:08:52.234
...all because of you!

68
00:08:52.410 --> 00:08:54.742
You're a numb-nut!

69
00:08:57.148 --> 00:08:58.479
Follow me!

70
00:09:07.158 --> 00:09:08.785
It's a stickup! Where's the money?

71
00:09:13.698 --> 00:09:15.893
Where's the money?

72
00:09:17.502 --> 00:09:19.629
What're you looking at? I'm serious!

73
00:09:24.576 --> 00:09:28.569
I kill people for less!
Give me the money.

74
00:09:46.998 --> 00:09:48.659
The money's in here.

75
00:10:24.602 --> 00:10:26.433
Let go of the girl!

76
00:10:39.451 --> 00:10:44.115
He's a fool. and she's mute. Losers!

77
00:11:27.599 --> 00:11:31.000
Go away! You're dragging me down!

78
00:11:31.769 --> 00:11:36.866
Go home and raise pigs.

79
00:11:41.779 --> 00:11:43.269
Go. before I kill you.

80
00:12:32.096 --> 00:12:35.497
You! Whatsyourname!

81
00:12:44.576 --> 00:12:48.012
Take this and get some new clothes.
You're now an Axe!

82
00:12:48.179 --> 00:12:52.013
- For real?
- Someone's waiting for you.

83
00:12:58.923 --> 00:13:00.083
Brother Sum!

84
00:13:00.258 --> 00:13:04.752
One look at you. and I knew
you'd do anything.

85
00:13:05.063 --> 00:13:06.052
Right!

86
00:13:06.230 --> 00:13:08.027
You just needed your chance.

87
00:13:08.800 --> 00:13:09.858
Damn right!

88
00:13:10.034 --> 00:13:11.695
We've an assignment for you.

89
00:13:11.869 --> 00:13:13.427
Anything. Brother Sum!

90
00:13:32.290 --> 00:13:35.282
"Research on abnormal people. "
What's that?

91
00:13:35.460 --> 00:13:37.257
A mental asylum.

92
00:13:43.001 --> 00:13:44.229
Soldiers!

93
00:13:44.402 --> 00:13:46.131
Boy Scouts!

94
00:13:46.304 --> 00:13:47.293
Tanks!

95
00:13:47.472 --> 00:13:49.440
No worries.

96
00:13:49.607 --> 00:13:53.236
When the Boy Scouts change shifts.
you have exactly five minutes.

97
00:13:53.411 --> 00:13:57.347
Follow the arrows on the map.
Go to the last cell...

98
00:13:57.515 --> 00:14:02.179
...and get the man inside there out.
Here's your tools.

99
00:14:08.092 --> 00:14:09.582
What about you guys?

100
00:14:09.761 --> 00:14:11.752
We're your lookouts.

101
00:14:23.107 --> 00:14:25.098
Five minutes. Hurry!

102
00:16:39.410 --> 00:16:44.245
The world's top killer
indeed looks the part!

103
00:16:45.283 --> 00:16:47.615
It's only a title.

104
00:16:47.785 --> 00:16:51.243
Cut the bullshit. We want two people
killed. Name your price.

105
00:16:51.789 --> 00:16:53.313
Name my what?

106
00:16:55.693 --> 00:17:00.960
I've killed so many trying to find
a worthy adversary.

107
00:17:01.299 --> 00:17:04.598
So far. I've never found one.

108
00:17:04.936 --> 00:17:06.767
That's why I stayed inside.

109
00:17:06.938 --> 00:17:11.341
Had I met my match.
I'd have been out long ago.

110
00:17:11.509 --> 00:17:13.977
If you find me a worthy opponent...

111
00:17:14.145 --> 00:17:16.443
...I'll do it for free. No charge!

112
00:17:18.616 --> 00:17:19.776
Do you have someone?

113
00:17:19.951 --> 00:17:25.184
Yes. Brilliant fighters who are
up to the challenge.

114
00:17:25.356 --> 00:17:27.688
But first. will you show us
some moves?

115
00:17:27.859 --> 00:17:30.919
Not that we don't trust you.
We want to see you in action.

116
00:17:31.295 --> 00:17:35.561
You numskulls aren't worthy!

117
00:17:40.071 --> 00:17:41.732
He doesn't look the part.

118
00:17:42.640 --> 00:17:47.839
The slippers are a little crappy.
But he'll clean up well.

119
00:17:48.012 --> 00:17:49.912
You sure you got the right guy?

120
00:17:50.081 --> 00:17:53.414
Absolutely. I swear I did
exactly what you told me.

121
00:17:54.719 --> 00:17:58.678
Please show us some moves.
Mr. Beast. Don't make it hard for me!

122
00:17:58.856 --> 00:18:00.483
You dumb or what?

123
00:18:01.325 --> 00:18:03.316
You know what this is. old man?

124
00:18:03.761 --> 00:18:06.195
Ever seen a fist this big?

125
00:18:06.364 --> 00:18:09.492
Don't force me to fight.
I scare myself when I fight!

126
00:18:09.667 --> 00:18:11.601
Really? Try me. then.

127
00:18:15.439 --> 00:18:17.600
Is he okay?

128
00:18:23.381 --> 00:18:25.941
So you say you can fight?

129
00:18:27.351 --> 00:18:28.340
Harder!

130
00:18:29.220 --> 00:18:30.209
Harder!

131
00:18:33.457 --> 00:18:34.788
Harder!

132
00:18:37.695 --> 00:18:41.187
You hit like that and call yourself
a gangster?

133
00:18:46.170 --> 00:18:47.467
A foreign gun!

134
00:19:13.130 --> 00:19:18.466
In the world of kung fu.
speed defines the winner.

135
00:19:22.573 --> 00:19:25.474
The Beast is the best of them all.

136
00:19:25.743 --> 00:19:29.406
The Axe Gang extends its respect!

137
00:20:11.188 --> 00:20:14.055
The real masters.
together in one room!

138
00:20:15.159 --> 00:20:19.357
Only the world's top killer...

139
00:20:19.530 --> 00:20:21.725
...has such an aura.

140
00:20:22.466 --> 00:20:23.694
Likewise.

141
00:20:24.301 --> 00:20:26.963
Could you two be the fated lovers...?

142
00:20:27.138 --> 00:20:28.127
Paris...

143
00:20:28.305 --> 00:20:29.397
...and Helen of Troy!

144
00:20:30.207 --> 00:20:31.868
A pleasure. indeed.

145
00:20:32.143 --> 00:20:35.977
We're here to deal
with the Axe Gang...

146
00:20:36.147 --> 00:20:37.876
...and only the Axe Gang.

147
00:20:39.817 --> 00:20:42.650
You should've killed me before.

148
00:20:42.987 --> 00:20:47.424
Now you're committing suicide.

149
00:20:47.591 --> 00:20:50.924
You're living on borrowed time.

150
00:20:51.095 --> 00:20:54.087
You can't escape your fate!

151
00:20:54.832 --> 00:20:57.164
What's this? A funeral bell?

152
00:20:58.002 --> 00:21:01.335
With the Beast here.
let's see whose funeral it is!

153
00:21:02.173 --> 00:21:03.902
So you're on their side?

154
00:21:04.075 --> 00:21:06.236
Don't get me wrong.

155
00:21:06.410 --> 00:21:10.005
I only want to kill you...

156
00:21:10.181 --> 00:21:13.082
...or be killed by you.

157
00:21:15.586 --> 00:21:17.554
What do you think?

158
00:21:17.721 --> 00:21:23.057
The good cannot coexist with the bad.
You can't escape your destiny.

159
00:21:23.694 --> 00:21:27.027
So be it. Let's do it.

160
00:21:28.032 --> 00:21:29.192
Okay.

161
00:21:30.734 --> 00:21:31.758
Let's do it!

162
00:21:51.889 --> 00:21:54.289
Piece of cake. I can handle this.

163
00:22:03.734 --> 00:22:06.601
Good try. but a little off target.

164
00:23:26.383 --> 00:23:28.044
The Lion's Roar?

165
00:26:08.912 --> 00:26:10.140
Wait!

166
00:26:11.315 --> 00:26:16.150
I didn't know the Lion's Roar
could be done with a speaker!

167
00:26:16.320 --> 00:26:18.652
What a blow!

168
00:26:47.951 --> 00:26:51.284
- Looks like they're not up to it!
- Let's get them while they're down.

169
00:26:51.455 --> 00:26:52.444
You do it!

170
00:26:52.623 --> 00:26:55.615
- I'm gonna puke! I need to see a doctor!
- Go to hell!

171
00:27:00.063 --> 00:27:01.860
You! Come over here.

172
00:27:02.866 --> 00:27:05.027
- Hit him!
- Yes!

173
00:27:09.473 --> 00:27:11.373
- The head!
- Of course!

174
00:27:11.542 --> 00:27:13.271
- Hit him on the head!
- Okay.

175
00:27:13.444 --> 00:27:15.241
- Here's your chance.
- Got it!

176
00:27:15.412 --> 00:27:16.538
- Hit him!
- Hit him!

177
00:27:16.713 --> 00:27:18.203
- Hit the shit out of him!
- Right!

178
00:27:18.382 --> 00:27:19.644
- Hit him!
- Hit him!

179
00:27:19.817 --> 00:27:21.580
Beat the shit out of him!

180
00:27:23.654 --> 00:27:24.643
What're you doing?

181
00:27:25.389 --> 00:27:28.324
You want me to hit him
or beat the shit out of him?

182
00:27:28.492 --> 00:27:30.426
You're making me very confused!

183
00:27:58.755 --> 00:28:01.747
Wow. that's a big fist!

184
00:28:34.324 --> 00:28:35.723
Why did you hit me?

185
00:29:04.655 --> 00:29:07.988
Where are they?

186
00:29:08.325 --> 00:29:10.486
How could you let them escape?

187
00:29:16.600 --> 00:29:20.593
No one gets away from me!

188
00:29:34.251 --> 00:29:36.446
Why did he save us?

189
00:29:36.620 --> 00:29:39.714
Young people make mistakes.

190
00:29:40.057 --> 00:29:43.823
But at least he finally made good.

191
00:29:44.394 --> 00:29:48.091
Look at him! Beaten to a pulp.

192
00:29:50.834 --> 00:29:54.133
Do you have any last requests?

193
00:30:13.423 --> 00:30:16.324
Hey. wait!

194
00:30:16.693 --> 00:30:20.527
Why don't you write in Chinese?
I don't understand.

195
00:31:16.887 --> 00:31:18.912
There's no one here!

196
00:31:23.694 --> 00:31:26.322
CHINESE MEDICINE

197
00:31:40.010 --> 00:31:43.002
It's a miracle he lasted this long.

198
00:31:43.680 --> 00:31:45.944
The herbs should help him.

199
00:31:46.183 --> 00:31:50.586
Herbal medicine can only partly help.
The key is his own body structure.

200
00:31:50.754 --> 00:31:55.088
All his bones and tendons are broken.

201
00:31:55.258 --> 00:31:58.193
It's amazing he's recovering so fast.

202
00:31:58.695 --> 00:32:00.856
It can't be possible...

203
00:32:01.031 --> 00:32:02.589
Unless he's...

204
00:32:39.936 --> 00:32:41.460
What's that smell?

205
00:33:15.472 --> 00:33:17.463
You mustn't smoke while you're hurt.

206
00:33:18.942 --> 00:33:20.432
Let me handle this.

207
00:33:35.225 --> 00:33:36.692
This makes no sense.

208
00:33:48.338 --> 00:33:52.399
Who knew the Beast could clear
the chi flow...

209
00:33:52.576 --> 00:33:55.136
...and thus unleash
the boy's true potential?

210
00:33:55.345 --> 00:33:58.246
We should've guessed.

211
00:33:59.482 --> 00:34:02.883
He is the one!

212
00:34:13.330 --> 00:34:15.264
Is this for real?

213
00:34:15.432 --> 00:34:17.992
You're still alive. you turncoat?

214
00:34:18.168 --> 00:34:20.568
Kill him. men!

215
00:35:15.425 --> 00:35:16.892
What kind of move is that?

216
00:35:17.227 --> 00:35:19.752
Kids' stuff!

217
00:35:47.657 --> 00:35:51.252
If our son were alive.
he'd be his age now.

218
00:35:51.428 --> 00:35:56.764
If he studies hard. he could grow up
to be a doctor or lawyer.

219
00:35:56.933 --> 00:35:59.766
A stuntman. more likely!

220
00:37:02.932 --> 00:37:04.490
Not bad. Let's go.

221
00:37:47.544 --> 00:37:49.603
I can even stop bullets...

222
00:38:59.983 --> 00:39:03.350
What? The Toad Style
of the Kwan Lun School?

223
00:39:03.520 --> 00:39:04.714
Oh. no!

224
00:41:00.303 --> 00:41:04.239
Remember the Palm move
that falls from heaven?

225
00:41:04.407 --> 00:41:07.570
That's the long lost Buddhist Palm.

226
00:41:51.888 --> 00:41:53.219
I surrender!

227
00:42:54.751 --> 00:42:56.184
What kind of move was that?

228
00:42:57.954 --> 00:43:00.115
If you want to learn. I'll teach you.

229
00:43:11.868 --> 00:43:13.199
Master!

230
00:44:27.043 --> 00:44:30.877
Hey! Tell him not to put snot
on the glass.

231
00:44:31.047 --> 00:44:33.641
You two. put your pants on!

232
00:44:33.816 --> 00:44:36.478
No licking if you're not buying!

233
00:45:42.852 --> 00:45:47.448
Kid. you have the bone structure
of a kung-fu genius.

234
00:45:47.623 --> 00:45:51.423
World peace is in your hands.
Here's the scroll of the Buddhist Palm.

235
00:45:51.594 --> 00:45:54.188
Because it's fate. I'll let you
have it for $ 10.

236
00:45:54.363 --> 00:45:55.421
Wait!

237
00:45:55.865 --> 00:45:58.265
You want more...?
